&lt;Shell Canada Ltd>, 72 pctowned by Royal Dutch/Shell Group, anticipates an improved levelof earnings in 1987, assuming a continuation of prices andmargins that existed at the end of 1986 and early 1987, thecompany said in the annual report.    Shell previously reported 1986 operating profit fell to 130mln dlrs, excluding a 24 mln dlr unusual gain, from 146 mlndlrs in the prior year.    The company also said 1987 capital and exploration spendingof 420 mln dlrs will be 160 mln dlrs lower than last year, dueto the uncertain short-term outlook.&#3;